The 1H inversion-recovery curves for both CH3 and NH3 at each temperature were fitted to exponentials to extract T1ρ. The data were well fitted a single exponential, indicating that there is one dominant relaxation mechanism acting per environment. Thus, T1ρ was determined by fitting the decay plots with the equation below26,27.1P(t)/P0=exp-t/T1ρ,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
